 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.453","title":"[audit][bin] Remove Debug formatting requirement from live semaphore cancel recovery assertion","description":"Fresh bounded audit child under asupersync-1qfd0. Current rch-backed `cargo check -p asupersync --features cli --all-targets` is blocked at src/bin/asupersync.rs:5595 because a bin test assertion formats `cancel_result` with `{:?}`, but Poll<Result<SemaphorePermit<'_>, AcquireError>> is not Debug. Scope: src/bin/asupersync.rs only. Replace the assertion/reporting pattern with one that preserves the test intent without requiring Debug on SemaphorePermit, then rerun rch-backed targeted validation. Do not widen into unrelated bin/runtime work.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AzureGate","created_at":"2026-03-27T05:40:22.920768896Z","created_by":"AzureGate","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:49:52.808764318Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:49:52.808408847Z","close_reason":"completed: current tree already carried the one-line bin assertion fix; rch check/clippy all-targets for -p asupersync --features cli now pass","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","bin","compile"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.453","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T05:40:22.920768896Z","created_by":"AzureGate","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2742,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.453","author":"AzureGate","text":"[2026-03-27 AzureGate] Validated this blocker as already satisfied in the current working tree. The local diff in src/bin/asupersync.rs removes the `{:?}` formatting from the live semaphore cancel-recovery assertion, which clears the prior `SemaphorePermit<'_>`-is-not-Debug compile failure.\n\nValidation:\n- rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check src/bin/asupersync.rs => PASS\n- rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/rch-target-azuregate-bin-check5 cargo check -p asupersync --fe