 {"id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5.3","title":"[WASM][RuntimeBuilder] Expose service/shared-worker runtime_context in fail-closed browser diagnostics","description":"Bounded child under asupersync-1sk16w.5. Today the Rust browser builder already exposes service/shared-worker host_role and fail-closed reason codes, but BrowserExecutionProbe and BrowserRuntimeSupportDiagnostics still collapse both hosts to runtime_context=unknown. Scope: teach the Rust-side execution-ladder diagnostics to classify service_worker and shared_worker explicitly while preserving the current fail-closed selected lane, reason codes, and not-yet-shipped support reasons. Update the maintained Rust browser fixture and contract tests accordingly. Non-goals: shipping real service/shared-worker direct-runtime lanes, changing packages/browser helper semantics, or touching active SharedWorker/service-worker coordinator implementation work.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageCove","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:08:28.894917435Z","created_by":"SageCove","updated_at":"2026-03-25T23:17:17.610858615Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T23:17:17.610492455Z","close_reason":"Completed targeted fixture/contract alignment and rch validation pass","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["browser","diagnostics","phase-1","runtime-builder","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:08:28.894917435Z","created_by":"SageCove","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5.4","title":"[WASM][Docs+Fixture] Propagate explicit service/shared-worker runtimeContext truth through Browser Edition contracts","description":"Bounded follow-on under asupersync-1sk16w.5. The Rust-side browser execution ladder now preserves explicit service_worker/shared_worker runtime_context values instead of collapsing those fail-closed hosts to unknown. Several maintained Browser Edition contract surfaces still encode the old unknown runtimeContext story. Scope: align docs/WASM.md, tests/wasm_js_exports_coverage_contract.rs, tests/fixtures/service-worker-broker-consumer/scripts/check-browser-run.mjs, and any directly supporting broker contract assertion so they require the explicit runtimeContext truth while preserving the unchanged fail-closed direct-runtime reason codes and bounded broker framing. Non-goals: shipping direct runtime on service/shared-worker hosts, changing package lane-selection policy, or touching active SharedWorker/service-worker implementation surfaces beyond contract drift.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageCove","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:21:10.476037933Z","created_by":"SageCove","updated_at":"2026-03-25T23:25:27.396445677Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T23:25:27.395953843Z","close_reason":"Completed explicit runtimeContext docs/fixture/service-worker broker contract alignment with rch validation pass","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["browser","docs","qa","serviceworker","sharedworker","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1sk16w.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:21:10.476037933Z","created_by":"SageCove","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1sk16w.6","title":"[HTTP][Body] Implement StreamBody as a real Body adapter","description":"`src/http/body.rs` exposes `StreamBody<S>` publicly and documents it as the adapter that turns a stream of frames into a `Body`, but the type currently only stores/returns the inner stream and has no `Body` implementation.

