- Emit a real `RemoteMessage::CancelRequest` envelope with origin metadata and logical time.
- Keep the no-runtime fallback deterministic and non-panicking.
- Add focused inline tests for the attached-runtime path and fallback path.
- Validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ChartreuseRidge","created_at":"2026-03-27T06:01:51.330456403Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T06:07:25.656298738Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T06:07:25.655838844Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in commit 46c95c46. abort() already sends RemoteMessage::CancelRequest via attached runtime with Cx authority and origin metadata. No-runtime fallback is a deterministic no-op. Tests exist.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cancellation","phase-1","remote"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1sk16w.8","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1sk16w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T06:01:51.330456403Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
